About the Oak
Colonial Oak Music Park
Historic downtown St. Augustine's most attractive and largest outdoor venue. Free concerts, private parties, weddings, and talent shows
The Colonial Oak Music Park is an outdoor venue on St George Street in Historic downtown St. Augustine, FL located under a majestic 300 year old oak tree. We pride ourselves as a
‚Äúcommunity
music park‚Äù which is why entrance to The Oak is almost always free to the public to sit and enjoy lunch, a drink or listen to live music. We feature some of North Florida‚Äôs best musical talent along with the occasional professional touring artists from many different genres of music on Thursday, Friday and Saturday evenings, as well as, Sunday afternoons. You can also rent the Oak space for your private events or weddings with full catering available too! If you are enjoying historic downtown, don‚Äôt miss a chance to experience a truly unique and beautiful outdoor venue! Soon, you too will be checking out our monthly calendar for upcoming events and telling your friends‚Ä¶‚ÄùSee U at the Oak!‚Äù

Reserve our Venue
Weddings and Special Occasions
Located in Historic Downtown Saint Augustine, the Colonial Oak is available
for your events, including weddings, corporate events and other private parties.
The Colonial Oak Music Park offers a truly magical and versatile setting in Historic St. Augustine, perfect for weddings, corporate events, and private gatherings. Nestled under the city‚Äôs second-oldest live oak tree, this one-of-a-kind venue features an amphitheater and family-style table seating for up to 175 guests, making it ideal for both intimate celebrations and larger parties. With its open-air charm and natural beauty, the space serves as a blank canvas, ready to be transformed into any bride‚Äôs dream vision‚Äîfrom rustic elegance to modern sophistication.
The venue also includes a full-service bar and customizable catering options prepared by our on-site chef, ensuring every detail reflects your personal style and taste. For a truly unforgettable experience, guests can enjoy entertainment from pirates or colonial-era reenactors, courtesy of the adjacent St. Augustine Pirate & Treasure Museum, available for a small additional fee. Whether you‚Äôre envisioning a classic celebration or a themed event, the Colonial Oak Music Park is the perfect backdrop for your special day.
Please contact our Event Coordinator for further information
